data.enText: a bridge that carries one road over another one

tr: a flight at a low altitude (usually of military aircraft) over spectators on the ground
bridge formed by the upper level of a crossing of two highways at different levels

value.def: A flyover is a structure which carries one road over the top of another road.

value.boxr_value: in AM, use 美国英语用overpass

value.def: A flyover is the same as a flypast .
